{
  "texts": [
    "The AI Act considers an AI system high risk if the AI is (a) a safety component of a product or is itself the product, and (b) that product is subject to third-party conformity assessment when being placed on the market, whereby both requirements refer to a listing of legislations in Annex II of the Act (AI Act, article 6(2)).",
    "High-risk areas of use include biometric identification, education, workers management, or asylum and border control management, see AI Act Annex III."
  ]
}